{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "note": "retained_via_interfaces located the entire narrowed-handle family I cited: the 11 authclient wrappers (lib/auth/authclient/api.go:1589-1917), the auth v1 service configs (crownjewelv1 Reader, notificationsv1 Backend, machineidv1 BotInstancesCache, workloadidentityv1 issuerCache, etc.), the lib/services/watcher.go getter-embedding configs, and the agent-side AccessPoint holders (lib/srv/app, lib/srv/db, lib/srv/desktop, lib/kube/proxy). None of these files name backend.Backend."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "cache.Cache (file: lib/cache/cache.go)", "note": "added holders the Backend blast missed: inventoryv1.Service/ServiceConfig via InventoryCache, recordingencryption.Manager/ManagerConfig via Cache, git.KeyManagerConfig via AccessPoint, web.sessionCache/sessionCacheOptions/SessionContextConfig via ReadProxyAccessPoint, lib/web/app/transport.go via ReadProxyAccessPoint, regular.Server via ReadProxyAccessPoint, access.Materializer via AssignmentStore. Also gave affected_via_composition for assignments.AssignmentCache:50 and roles.RoleCache:39."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "note": "affected_via_composition and affected_subclasses gave correct refs for the lib/services/local/* services and storage.ProcessStorage (lib/auth/storage/storage.go:82), which I cited in group 1."},
    {"tool": "sense_status", "query": "(no args)", "note": "confirmed the Go index was full-tier, fresh (pending 0, watching) and covered 5719 Go files, so I trusted the blast enumeration as the audit spine rather than sampling by hand."}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "cluster state storage backend read watch cache resources", "note": "Did not surface backend.Backend or lib/cache.Cache at all. Top hits were lib/teleterm/clusteridcache, lib/auth/storage/storage.go stateBackend, and per-collection cache constructors. I picked the actual target (backend.Backend + cache.Cache) from prior knowledge of Teleport, not from this result."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "note": "retained_via_interfaces refs point at the STRUCT DECLARATION line, not the retaining field line the ticket asked for. e.g. it gave lib/srv/app/server.go:58 for app.Config via AppsAccessPoint, but the AccessPoint field is at :66; lib/kube/proxy/forwarder.go:116 but CachingAuthClient is at :128; lib/web/sessions.go:703 but accessPoint is at :707. I had to grep every single one."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "note": "Missed lib/services/watcher.go:1930 GitServerWatcherConfig / GitServerGetter, which is structurally identical to the 15 sibling watcher configs it did return. I found it only by grepping the embedded-getter pattern across the file."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "note": "Large false-positive tier: ~40% of the 375 rows are audit-log/streaming holders (events.SessionWriter via Stream, events.MultiLog via AuditLogger, filesessions.UploaderConfig via Streamer, eventstest.MockUploader via MultipartUploader) that 'retain' storage only because carrier auth.Server composes it. I had to manually filter these out of the audit."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend (include_tests: false)", "note": "include_tests:false did not exclude test files from retained_via_interfaces — page 3 (offset 241) was over half *_test.go rows (accesslist.mockClient, auth_test.mockCache, proxy.mockAccessPoint...), and the offset-363 tail was 12/12 test rows. The flag appears to gate affected_tests only."}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend + cache.Cache retained_via_interfaces", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "Field-level line numbers. Refs anchored to the struct decl, so I ran three bulk greps (~70 file+type pairs) to recover the actual retaining field lines — this was the single largest chunk of the session."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "Completeness within an obvious family. Grepping '^\\t[A-Za-z]+Getter$' over lib/services/watcher.go surfaced GitServerGetter at :1930, absent from the retained set."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "cache.Cache", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Whether a 'composes Cache' row means a concrete pointer field or something else. I sed'd lib/scopes/cache/assignments/assignment_cache.go:49-54 and roles/role_cache.go:38-42 to confirm they hold *cache.Cache[...] generics from lib/scopes/cache, a DIFFERENT Cache than lib/cache.Cache — the blast did not disambiguate which of the two same-named types it had traversed."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "cache.Cache", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Confirmation that InventoryCacheConfig holds storage twice. Reading lib/cache/inventory/inventory_cache.go:325-350 showed both PrimaryCache *cache.Cache (:327) and BotInstanceBackend services.BotInstance (:339); the retained row listed only the BotInstance path."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Field type for holders where my type-anchored grep returned nothing — sed/grep on discoveryconfigv1, healthcheckconfigv1, vnetconfigv1, x509_overrides_service, appauthconfigv1, scopes/access, scopes/joining showed the fields are named 'Backend'/'Storage'/'Reader' with a services.* qualified type, which my first regex pass missed."}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query_before": "cache.Cache (direction: callers)", "query_after": "sense_blast cache.Cache with file: \"lib/cache/cache.go\"", "hint": "\"Multiple symbols named 'cache.Cache' exist — retry this tool with the `file` parameter set to the path of the one you want... top_matches: cache.Cache (170 edges) lib/cache/cache.go:532, cache.Cache (6 edges) lib/scopes/cache/cache.go:91\". This told me there were two Caches and which was the real one, and I carried the file param over to blast instead of re-running graph."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "query_before": "sense_blast backend.Backend (no offset)", "query_after": "sense_blast backend.Backend offset:114, then 241, then 363", "hint": "\"retained_trimmed\": true with \"retained_next_offset\": 114 and \"Pages are unionable only while retained_index_fingerprint is unchanged\" — I paged all 375 rows and checked the fingerprint (f8683@2026-07-19) stayed constant across pages so I could safely union them."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "query_before": "trusting the retained list as-is", "query_after": "grep-verifying a sample of ~12 holders, then all of them", "hint": "\"index_caveat: Static graph may miss: method-on-field dispatch (c.engine.X), function-value passing... interface satisfaction via blank identifier\" plus the project instruction to spot-check list outputs. The spot-check is what exposed the struct-line-vs-field-line gap and led to the bulk grep passes."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend offset:363", "query_before": "max_hops:3 with full context", "query_after": "max_hops:1, context_lines:0", "hint": "\"snippets_truncated\": true and the sheer response size on the first two pages — I dropped hops and snippets on later pages to get the tail rows without blowing context, and the tail page then included the useful via_satisfiers field that earlier pages omitted."}
  ],
  "q4_value": "retained_via_interfaces is the whole reason this audit was tractable. The ticket's hard case — a holder whose field is a locally declared interface, in a file that never imports lib/backend or lib/cache and never names their types — is invisible to grep by construction: there is no string to search for. Sense gave me ~130 such holders across 9 areas in four paged calls, including families I would not have thought to look for (the 11 authclient per-role wrappers, the 37 auth v1 services each with its own bespoke Cache/Reader/Backend interface). Grep could only have found these by me first guessing every interface name, which is circular.",
  "q5_improve": "Anchor retained_via_interfaces refs to the retaining FIELD, not the struct declaration — and emit the field name and its declared type alongside. The ticket asked for 'the file:line of its retaining field', and the tool gave me the struct line, so I spent the majority of the session running bulk greps to convert ~70 struct refs into field refs (server.go:58→:66, forwarder.go:116→:128, sessions.go:703→:707). The tool already knows which field created the edge; surfacing it would have made the output directly citable and cut this session roughly in half. Secondary: make include_tests:false actually filter retained_via_interfaces, and rank or flag the auth.Server-carrier rows whose via is an audit/streaming interface so the storage-relevant signal isn't diluted ~40%.",
  "score": 8,
  "score_rationale": "Per Q1/Q4, Sense surfaced the interface-typed holders that are unfindable by grep in principle — no literal to search for — which is 9-10 territory, but per Q1/Q2 every one of the ~130 refs needed a grep pass to convert struct lines into the field lines the task demanded, it silently dropped GitServerWatcherConfig from an otherwise complete family, and ~40% of rows were audit-log noise I filtered by hand, so it lands at the top of the 'faster, but I still needed fallbacks to finish' band rather than above it."
}

